# .cursorignore — strategic exclusion for token reduction.
# Removes low-signal, high-token content from the agent's default context.
# See AGENTS.md "Token discipline". Keep this list aggressive.

# === Lockfiles (read via package manager, not by agent) ===
**/uv.lock
**/package-lock.json
**/pnpm-lock.yaml
**/yarn.lock
**/poetry.lock
**/Cargo.lock
**/go.sum

# === Build / generated artifacts ===
**/.next/
**/out/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/.turbo/
**/.swc/
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/next-env.d.ts

# === Python ===
**/__pycache__/
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/htmlcov/
**/.coverage
**/coverage.xml
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.pyright/
**/*.egg-info/

# === Node ===
**/node_modules/
**/.eslintcache

# === Logs and temp ===
**/*.log
**/*.tmp
**/*.bak
**/.DS_Store

# === Binary / media assets (do not embed) ===
**/*.png
**/*.jpg
**/*.jpeg
**/*.gif
**/*.webp
**/*.ico
**/*.svg
**/*.mp4
**/*.mov
**/*.pdf
**/*.zip
**/*.tar.gz

# === Project-specific exclusions ===
# Original product brief (~110 KB). Distilled into docs/BACKLOG.md.
# Read via `rg "STORY X.Y" chat-plan.md -A 20` only if BACKLOG.md is insufficient.
chat-plan.md

# Generated DB schema dumps / migrations data
**/alembic/versions/*.sql

# Coverage and test reports
**/test-results/
**/playwright-report/
**/*.coverage

# IDE / OS
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# Large data fixtures
**/fixtures/large/
**/seed-data/dumps/
